<TITLE> Trust Bank certified for merchant banking </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)Trust Bank Limited has been certified for merchant banking operations, according to a declaration posted on the Dhaka Stock Exchange website Wednesday. The bank has announced that it hopes to start merchant banking by the end of March. Trust Bank, a private commercial bank, was incorporated in June 1999 as a public limited company under the Companies Act 1994. It conducts all types of commercial banking activities. The bank was established under the sponsorship of the Army Welfare Trust. The bank's initial paid-up capital was Tk 200 million50 percent held by Army Welfare Trust designated as group-A shareholder. No officials, including public relations officer, of the bank were available to comment. bdne
